{
  "local_port": 60338,
  "remote_port": 443,
  "prompt": "I keep getting dock connected on my Android, how do I get it off?",
  "response": "If you're repeatedly seeing a \"dock connected\" notification on your Android device and you want to remove or stop it, here are several steps you can take to address the issue:\n\n### 1. **Check Physical Connections**\n\n- **Remove All Cables and Accessories:**\n  - Ensure that your device isn't physically connected to any dock, charger, or accessory that might be triggering the dock detection.\n  - Sometimes, even partially inserted cables can cause the device to think it's docked.\n\n- **Inspect the Docking Port:**\n  - Examine the USB-C or micro-USB port (depending on your device) for any debris, dust, or damage.\n  - Use a soft brush or compressed air to clean out the port gently.\n\n### 2. **Restart Your Device**\n\n- **Simple Restart:**\n  - Sometimes, a simple restart can resolve temporary glitches.\n  - Hold down the power button and select \"Restart\" from the menu.\n\n### 3. **Disable Dock-Related Notifications**\n\n- **Access Notification Settings:**\n  1. Open the **Settings** app on your device.\n  2. Go to **Apps & notifications** (this may vary slightly depending on your Android version).\n  3. Tap on **See all apps** or **App info**.\n  4. Look for system apps like **System UI**, **Phone**, or any app related to docks or accessories.\n  5. Tap on the relevant app and then select **Notifications**.\n  6. Find the **Dock** notification and toggle it off.\n\n- **Alternative Path:**\n  - Some devices allow you to long-press the notification itself when it appears and select \u201cBlock\u201d or \u201cSilent\u201d.\n\n### 4. **Disable or Uninstall Dock-Related Apps**\n\n- **Identify Dock-Related Apps:**\n  - Some manufacturers include specific apps to manage docking functions (e.g., Samsung\u2019s \u201cGear\u201d app).\n  \n- **Disable the App:**\n  1. Go to **Settings > Apps & notifications > See all apps**.\n  2. Find the dock-related app.\n  3. Tap **Disable**. If the option isn't available, you might need to force stop it or restrict its permissions.\n\n- **Uninstall Updates:**\n  - If you can\u2019t disable the app, sometimes uninstalling updates can help.\n  - Tap on **Uninstall updates** within the app info screen.\n\n### 5. **Check for Wireless Docking or Bluetooth Connections**\n\n- **Disable Wireless Features:**\n  - If your device supports wireless docking via Bluetooth or Wi-Fi, ensure these are turned off.\n  \n- **Forget Bluetooth Devices:**\n  1. Go to **Settings > Bluetooth**.\n  2. Look for any devices that might be related to docking.\n  3. Tap the gear icon next to them and select **Forget** or **Unpair**.\n\n### 6. **Boot into Safe Mode**\n\n- **Determine if a Third-Party App is Causing the Issue:**\n  1. Press and hold the power button until the power menu appears.\n  2. Press and hold the **Power Off** option until a prompt to reboot into safe mode appears.\n  3. Tap **OK** to confirm.\n  4. In Safe Mode, observe if the \"dock connected\" notification still appears.\n     - **If it doesn\u2019t**: A third-party app is likely causing the issue. Consider uninstalling recently installed apps.\n     - **If it does**: The problem may be system-related.\n\n- **Exit Safe Mode:**\n  - Simply restart your device to exit Safe Mode.\n\n### 7. **Update Your Device\u2019s Software**\n\n- **Ensure Your Device is Up to Date:**\n  1. Go to **Settings > System > Advanced > System update**.\n  2. Check for updates and install any available.\n\n### 8. **Factory Reset (Last Resort)**\n\n- **Backup Important Data First:**\n  - Performing a factory reset will erase all data on your device.\n\n- **Perform the Reset:**\n  1. Go to **Settings > System > Advanced > Reset options**.\n  2. Select **Erase all data (factory reset)**.\n  3. Follow the on-screen instructions to complete the reset.\n\n**Note:** Only perform a factory reset if all other steps fail to resolve the issue.\n\n### 9. **Seek Professional Help**\n\n- **Contact Manufacturer Support:**\n  - If the problem persists after trying all the above steps, there might be a hardware issue.\n  - Reach out to your device manufacturer\u2019s customer support or visit an authorized service center for assistance.\n\n### Additional Tips:\n\n- **Use Diagnostic Apps:**\n  - Some devices have built-in diagnostic tools. For example, on many Android devices, you can access a hidden diagnostic menu by dialing `*#*#4636#*#*` in the phone app.\n  \n- **Check for Recent Changes:**\n  - If the issue started after installing a new app or updating your device, consider reverting those changes.\n\nBy following these steps, you should be able to identify and resolve the issue causing the \"dock connected\" notification on your Android device.",
